<item>
            <title>[LANG-1727] EventListenerSupport doesn&apos;t document ordering of events</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LANG-1727</link>
                <project id="12310481" key="LANG">Commons Lang</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;org.apache.commons.lang3.event.EventListenerSupport needs to document and test for:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. The synchronicity of events; i.e. they&apos;re not fired in separate threads simultaneously&lt;br/&gt;
2. The ordering of events&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Adding A, B, and C to EventListenerSupport shouldn&apos;t leave devs wondering whether the events are fired A, B, C or B, C, A or C, B, A.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
